  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to explore the skeletal effect of Thai traditional massage by
      examining the changes in biochemical markers of bone turnover immediately after the massage.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Each subject received Thai traditional massage for 2 hours by a single masseuse.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
